	<h1>0wnz0red</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Salon.com: <a href="http://salon.com/tech/feature/2002/08/28/0wnz0red/print.html">&#8220;0wnz0red&#8221;</a> by Cory Doctorow. &#8220;Programmers who hack their own bodies don&#8217;t need exercise and never get sick: A new short story from one of science fiction&#8217;s bright young stars.&#8221; </p>

<p><a href="http://boingboing.net/2002_08_01_archive.html#85388539">Cory sez:</a> &#8220;This is, AFAIK, the first original fiction Salon&#8217;s published [&#8230;] the first example of a new genre called &#8216;Nerdc0re&#8217;&#8221;. Mega props, Cory!</p>

<p>I&#8217;ve been writing a short nerdc0re story but I fear it sucks and doesn&#8217;t do the tech justice. Unfortunately for me it seems that a short story is the best way to explain it.</p>

